    "recap_headline": "University of Connecticut Athletics",
    "recap_text": "STORRS, Conn.\n- The UConn baseball team (7-9) lost 26-19 to Boston College (10-6) in a four-hour, 31 minute nine-inning affair at Elliot Ballpark.\nThe Huskies offense scored a season-high 19 runs on 19 hits with six\u00a0Huskies recording multi-hit games.\nNater Wachter\nled the way with a four-hit day and drove in three.\nJunior\nTyler Minick\nmade his return to the lineup after missing 12 games with injury and went 3-5 with three runs scored and three RBI that featured his first home run of the season, a two-run shot.\nBryce Detwiler\n3-4 at the plate with four runs batted in, all coming off the bench for the freshman.\u00a0That included\u00a0hitting his first career home run in the fourth and bases-clearing double in the seventh.\nUConn put together its highest scoring inning of the season with an eight spot in the seventh inning that saw 13 Huskies come to the plate.\nThe Huskies eight extra base hits was the most in a game this season.\nUConn\u00a0threw 10 pitchers on Tuesday and only one,\nFrank Spirito IV\n, threw a scoreless inning. RHP\nJoe Talarico\nand RHP\nRyan Tatar\neach made their UConn debut on Tuesday while veteran LHP\nSam Hutchinson\nmade his season debut on his return from injury.\nNext up, the Huskies will begin a nine games in 10 days spring break trip in Portland against the Portland Pilots on Friday, March 13 at 9 p.m. ET / 6 p.m. PT"
